    <item>
      <title>Adaptavist - Getting Started with GitLab</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/talks/gitlabadaptavist/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 20 Mar 2024 18:50:38 -0500</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/talks/gitlabadaptavist/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div style=&#34;position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;iframe allow=&#34;accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share; fullscreen&#34; loading=&#34;eager&#34; referrerpolicy=&#34;strict-origin-when-cross-origin&#34; src=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/embed/3jFAUX1N30M?autoplay=0&amp;amp;controls=1&amp;amp;end=0&amp;amp;loop=0&amp;amp;mute=0&amp;amp;start=0&#34; style=&#34;position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border:0;&#34; title=&#34;YouTube video&#34;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In this live webinar, Josiah Tillett (Adaptavist) and Bart Zhang (GitLab) explore the full range of GitLab&amp;rsquo;s features, covering everything from basic version control to pipelines and advanced code analysis tools. Plus, they discuss how GitLab can use DevOps and pipeline automation to increase consistency, reduce errors and shorten the time it takes to get code changes through to production.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
